LONG DESC: The Kitchen is an absolute mess. Culinary equipment covers the countertops and old menus and orders are strewn across the floor. The sink has a leaky faucet, yet still there seems to be dirty dishes there that have kept their grime all these years. With all this clutter, there may be something useful hidden. There are two door in the kitchen. One is on the west wall and the other the east wall.
SHORT DESC: The kitchen sink has some dish soap on the side that might come in handy. It might be helpful to start cleaning the place up to put things in the right order.
ADITIONAL DESC: You can barely make out something unusual at the bottom of the sink. Try cleaning the dishes to find out what it is.
